article.headline: Cornell 61, Brown 59
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Andrew Naeve had 11 points and 12 rebounds to lead Cornell in a 61-59 win over Brown Friday. Ryan Wittman and Louis Dale each contributed 14 points for Cornell (12-9, 5-2 Ivy). Mark McAndrew had 17 points and 13 rebounds for Brown (7-15, 2-5). Damon Huffman and Marcus Becker each added 11 points for Brown. McAndrew's last second shot for Brown from behind the three-point arc missed its mark, sealing the win for Cornell. A sloppy first half was tied, 25-all, when the two teams exchanged three-point baskets in the final two seconds. Cornell finished with a 35 percent shooting average and just 4-of-18 point attempts. Brown shot 40 percent from the field. Cornell outrebounded Brown 44-32.
